Here is an implementation of `extract_julia_code` function in Julia:

```julia
function extract_julia_code(md::AbstractString)
    # Find all code blocks in the markdown document
    matches = eachmatch(r"```julia.*?\n(.*?)\n```", md, seed=1);

    # Store the code blocks found and join them with newline
    code_blocks = [match.captures[1] for match in matches];
    result = join([code for code in code_blocks], "\n") * "\n";

    return result;
end
```
Please note, this function assumes that the julia language code blocks are correctly formatted and don't contain any nested `code fences`. It also does not check for the presence of closing triple back-ticks. If there could be such a scenario, you might want to add error handling or additional logic to handle those cases.
